      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:5:2:109:1",
      "text": [
        " سَأَلْتُهُ عَنِ الرَّهْنِ وَ الْكَفِيلِ فِي بَيْعِ النَّسِيئَةِ فَقَالَ لَا بَأْسَ بِهِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "A number of our companions, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad, from Ali Bin Al Hakam, from Muhammad Bin Muslim, from Abu Hamza, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Ja’far<sup>asws</sup>, said, ‘I asked him<sup>asws</sup> about the mortgage and the guarantor regarding a sale on credit. So he<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘There is no problem with it’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "1. A number of our people have narrated from Ahmad ibn Muhammad from Ali ibn al-Hakam from Muhammad ibn Muslim from abu Hamzah who has said the following: “I once asked abu Ja’far, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, about security deposit, mortgage and guarantor in transaction on credit. He (the Imam) said, ’It is not unlawful.”’ "
        ]
      }
    },
